title: Manchester City see big future for Aaron Mooy after turning down $11m offer | Football | Sporting News
text:
January 30, 2017 3:36am EST January 30, 2017 2:55am EST Could we see Aaron Mooy play in the Premier League for Manchester City? Sporting News 
Published on Jan. 30, 2017 
Jan. 30, 2017 
England football giants Manchester City have reportedly turned down an offer of $11m for Aaron Mooy from an unnamed Championship club. 
MORE: FFA deny A-League players suffered heat stroke 
The Socceroo is currently on loan at Huddersfield Town and attracting attention from another 'high-flying club' in the league, but there is no sign of City cashing in on the former Melbourne City star. 
According to beIN Sports, the Sky Blues were considering recallling Mooy as cover for Fernandinho after impressing Pep Guardiola. 
With the January transfer window closing at 10am on Wednesday morning there may be another last-ditch bid for Mooy.
